hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: When do you want me to start? rawpharma.com We are told that HS2 from London to Birmingham will take 49 minutes instead of the current 84. But if a 30-minute minimum check-in time is applied, as with HS1, that will increase the journey time to 79 minutes, a saving of only five minutes. Furthermore, as HS2 trains will be much longer than conventional trains, passengers at the rear will face a longer walk at their destination, reducing the overall saving to only three or four minutes. That seems to me like Â£70 billion badly spent.
